    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Historical Information
</head>
      <p>Amherst County was formed from Albemarle County in 1761. Islands in the Fluvanna (now the James) River were added in 1770. The county is named for Major General Jeffery Amherst, British commander in North America during the later part of the French and Indian War and governor of Virginia from 1759-1768.
</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>Amherst County (Va.) Land Records consists of Liber Index to Deed Books, 1761-1846, which covers volumes A-Z.
</p>
    </scopecontent>
